<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="804" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/3362a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-02">December 2,
                                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2987. American interests—Far East. Inform Japanese Foreign Office
                                that <hi rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> arrived New York, December
                                    l.<note n="63" xml:id="d804fn63">The <hi rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> arrived at Port Elizabeth at 7:30 a.m.,
                                    South African summer time, November 3, and departed the next day
                                    at 6:30 p.m. The vessel arrived at Rio de Janeiro at 1:05 p.m.,
                                    November 15, and departed for New York on the 16th. For
                                    arrangements made at the New York pier and general observations,
                                    see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                                    November 13, 1943, pp. 320, 321. For the Department’s press
                                    release of January 13, 1944, on the exchange, see <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., January 15, 1944, p. 77.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>